# Rasm C# Production

**Required**: Read `coding-csharp` skill (`.claude/skills/coding-csharp/SKILL.md` or `~/.codex/skills/coding-csharp/SKILL.md`).

## Architecture trinity

1. **Singular OOP boundary** — one sealed capsule per native integration (`RasmCommand`, `RhinoUi.Use`, `GhUi`, etc.)
2. **Unified rails** — one of `Fin<T>`, `Validation<Error,T>`, `Eff<RT,T>` per file; no mixing
3. **Dense FP internals** — exhaustive `switch`, `[Union]`/`SmartEnum`, folds; zero domain `if`/`while`/`try`

## Library-specific AGENTS.md

| Library | File |
|---------|------|
| All libs | `libs/csharp/AGENTS.md` |
| Rasm core | `libs/csharp/Rasm/AGENTS.md` |
| Rhino boundary | `libs/csharp/Rasm.Rhino/AGENTS.md` |
| GH2 boundary | `libs/csharp/Rasm.Grasshopper/AGENTS.md` |
| Materials catalogue | `libs/csharp/Rasm.Materials/AGENTS.md` |

## Hard rules

- Zero `var`; explicit types everywhere
- No helper/utility files (`*Helper`, `*Util`, `common.*`)
- No wrapper-only RhinoCommon/GH2 renames
- Extend canonical owners before new files/types
- File sections: `TYPES` → `MODELS` → `CONSTANTS` → `ERRORS` → `SERVICES` → `OPERATIONS` → `COMPOSITION` → `EXPORTS`
- Boundary adapters only: `// BOUNDARY ADAPTER — reason` for required imperative/native code

## Validation

```bash
bash scripts/check-cs.sh check
```

Fix CSP#### violations architecturally. Run `full` only when `Directory.Build.props`, `Directory.Packages.props`, `.editorconfig`, or `Workspace.slnx` change.
